<AbstractNarration>The Fields Institute will mount an intensive program on Operator&lt;br/&gt;Algebras and Applications during the period July through December 2007. A large number&lt;br/&gt;of researchers and postdoctoral fellows will be in residence at the Institute&lt;br/&gt;during this period, and more will visit during the program's three workshops. A&lt;br/&gt;significant number of postdoctoral fellows will visit the Firelds Institute for the entire program.&lt;br/&gt;The Fields Institute will fund the program and support it logistically. This application&lt;br/&gt;uses funding from the NSF to bring US mathematicians to this&lt;br/&gt;program and support them while they are there. The funds are used principally to support&lt;br/&gt;mathematicians, especially junior mathematicians, who do not have other sources of support.</AbstractNarration>
